<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf64ac42c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s103"><num value="103">§ 103.</num><heading> Boundary Line</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this title, the term “Boundary Line” means a line established under <ref href="/us/act/1895-02-19/s2/b">section 2(b) of the Act of February 19, 1895</ref> (<ref href="/us/usc/t33/s151/b">33 U.S.C. 151(b)</ref>).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf64ac42d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s4">Pub. L. 109–304, § 4</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1486">120 Stat. 1486</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/114/120/tIII/s306/a/1">Pub. L. 114–120, title III, § 306(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="2016-02-08">Feb. 8, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/54">130 Stat. 54</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
